README for Amos2020_GLOBE git repo

REVISION HISTORY
27 Feb 2020 - README v1.0 created
28 Feb 2020 - Update 'How to run the code'

CITATION
Amos, H.M. and M.J. Starke et al., 2020, GLOBE Observer
Data:2016-2019, in prep. *Check back for updated journal
information and publication DOI*

CORRESPONDING AUTHOR
Helen Amos, helen.m.amos@nasa.gov

DISCLAIMER
This code comes as is without guarantees of any kind. 

CODE DESCRIPTION
This code generates the analysis and figures for the
journal article Amos & Starke et al. (2020).

SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS
Python 3
Anaconda 3 distribution, https://www.anaconda.com/distribution/

DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT
Spyder 3, https://www.spyder-ide.org/

HOW THE CODE IS ORGANIZED
main.py                : A wrapper script and the main driver
                         of the code.
make_fig0*.py          : Scripts to create the figures from
                         Amos & Starke et al. (2020)
stats_for_paper.py     : Calculate and print statistics for
                         Amos & Starke et al. (2020)
data_common.py         : Read in the observations and set up
                         global variables for analyzing
			 observations
figure_common.py       : Set up global variables for plotting
globeqa/plotters.py    : Utilities for plotting
globeqa/tools.py       : Utilities for reading and parsing data
globeqa/observation.py : Utilities for manipulating observations

HOW TO RUN THE CODE IN SPYDER
1. Open main.py

2. Run main.py

   Tip: Click the green arrow in the toolbar ribbon at the top.

3. Open data_common.py

4. In data_common.py, modify startdate and/or enddate to your
   desired date range (lines 30-31).

   Tip: The GLOBE API limits queries to 1 million observations.
        If your query fails, try a smaller date range. 